<abstract>
<p>Countertransference themes which developed in therapeutic and research relationships with torturers are described and explored. They include dysregulated affect, a sense of role reversal, disconnection from others, anger, a sense of betraying victims and the disruption of long-held beliefs. Ways of dealing with countertransference in relation to perpetrators are also discussed.</p>
</abstract>
